title: Kendall + Kylie Fashion Line, Tory Burch and Hillary Clinton - Style.com News
text:
Kylie and Kendall Jenner modeling their collection for Topshop
Photo: Courtesy of Topshop
The Jenner sisters get into the clothing business…
The Kardashian-Jenner empire has just gotten a little bit bigger. Kendall and Kylie Jenner are releasing their own fashion collection for the Spring 2016 season. The sisters hope their brand, called Kendall + Kylie, will give consumers a taste of the Jenner lifestyle without requiring a Jenner-sized income: Most items will cost under $100. [ WWD ]
Street style on the street…
The fashion world may seem to be populated entirely by the glamorous and wealthy, but appearances are deceiving. Mark Reay, for instance, was homeless for five years, even as he worked as a photographer for Dazed . A new film explores the wild contrasts in his life. [ Dazed ]
Tory hosts Hillary…
Tory Burch will invite Hillary Clinton to her Southampton home next month for a fundraiser. Want to join in? That will cost you at least $1,000, not including a photo op with the candidate. That will cost you another $1,700. [ Page Six ]
Cara’s not done yet…
When Cara Delevingne started acting and left her modeling agency, Storm Models, many of us assumed her modeling days were over. Happily, however, she now assures us that that is not the case. Just don’t expect her to take a break from the big screen anytime soon: “Maybe I’ll do fashion sometimes, but at the moment I have no time to do anything,” she said. [ The Hollywood Reporter ]
Behind the bad blood…
The model mania in Taylor Swift’s “Bad Blood” video will never end. Swift has been posting behind-the-scenes footage from the making of the “Bad Blood” video on her Instagram, showing models and actors teaching Swift how to ride motorcycles and be a spy. [ Billboard ]
